Class Town

  • java.lang.Object
    • Town
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Town>

    public class Town
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Town>
    Represents an town as a node of a graph. The Town class holds the name of the town and a list of adjacent towns, and other fields as desired, and the traditional methods (constructors, getters/setters, toString, etc.). It will implement the Comparable interface These are the minimum methods that are needed.
    Author:
    Derek Luong
